data.title: News
data.text: U.S. Marines and Sailors with 1st Marine Division train with French soldiers during Marara 24 in Tahiti, French Polynesia, May 31-June 7, 2024. Marara is a multinational training exercise that enhances combined interoperability between the U.S. military and France’s Combined Joint Task Force Headquarters in French Polynesia. The training advances partners’ abilities to address complex and future contingencies throughout the Indo-Pacific. (U.S. Marine Corps photo by Cpl. Willow Marshall)
